ope> </bibl> (anap.). </sense> <sense n=\"II\" id=\"n62593.3\" level=\"2\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">talk</tr_> or <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">gossip</tr_>, such as went on in the <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λέσχαι</foreign> (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λεσχηνεύω</foreign>, etc.), <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">μακραὶ λ.</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0006.tlg005.perseus-grc1:384\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ E.\">E.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hipp.\">Hipp.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">384</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0006.tlg018.perseus-grc1:1001\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IA\">IA</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1001</biblScope> </bibl> (pl.), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0451.tlg001:11:32\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Epicr.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">11.32</biblScope> </bibl> (pl., anap.), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0527.tlg029:23:29\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ LXX\">LXX</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pr.\">Pr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23.29</biblScope> </bibl> (pl.), <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">AP</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">13.6</biblScope> </bibl> (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Phal.\">Phal.</a></author> </bibl>); in bad sense, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">malicious gossip, scandal</tr_>, Vett. Val.in <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Cat.Cod.Astr.</title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">8(1).165</biblScope> </bibl> (p